Emma: It's tragic how he was burned to death. His overwhelming desire to avenge his daughter pushed him to create something beyond his own control. #line:ch006_great_church_55
Emma:It's quite sad... #line:ch006_great_church_55_1
Roman: Perhaps the tale was preserved to teach us not to succumb to anger. #line:ch006_great_church_56
Roman: The Saint may have faltered, but perhaps Mr. {GetPlayerName()}, with his heroic spirit, can harness and command the immense energy of that 'Ring of Destruction'. #line:ch006_great_church_56_1
Roman: With the 'Ring of Destruction', based on the information gathered by Mr. {GetPlayerName()} and the group, we could amplify our strength against the great demons. #line:ch006_great_church_57
Roman:  It might even provide the edge we need to defeat Hades or whatever he truly is. #line:ch006_great_church_57_1
Emma: ... Against the great evil.... #line:ch006_great_church_58
Emma: Then when everyone recovers, let's get ready and head to the Cursed Mansion to get the 'Ring of Destruction'. #line:ch006_great_church_59
